This paper is about deep learning models for speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and audio processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses training efficiency and optimization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning models for speech recognition is a common application of artificial intelligence (AI), which could make cs.AI a possible sub-category as well.
